 League first qualifying round]] \n|note_res_EL1=[[FK Daugava Daugavpils|Daugava Daugavpils]] won the [[Latvian Football Cup 2008]] competition, thereby qualifying for [[2009\u201310 UEFA Europa League#Second qualifying round|UEFA Europa League 2009\u201310 second qualification round]]. However, Daugava Daugavpils merged with [[Dinaburg FC|Dinaburg]], so the Europa League spots were redistributed based on league position. \n|result4=EL1\n\n|update=complete\n|source=[http://www.lff.lv/lv/virsliga/vesture/2008/tabula/ Latvian Football Federation] {{in lang|lv}} \n|class_rules=1) points; 2) head-to-head points; 3) head-to-head goal difference; 4) head-to-head goals scored; 5) goal difference; 6) number of goals scored.\n}}\n\n====Results====\n{{#invoke:Sports results|main\n|matches_style=FBR|solid_cell=grey\n|team1=DGD|team2=DIN|team3=LIE|team4=R\u012aG|team5=SKO\n|team6=VEN\n\n|name_DGD=[[FC Daugava|FC Daugava Daugavpils]]\n|match_DGD_DIN=2\u20130\n|match_DGD_LIE=1\u20132\n|match_DGD_R\u012aG=2\u20130\n|match_DGD_SKO=2\u20131\n|match_DGD_VEN=0\u20132\n\n|name_DIN=[[Dinaburg FC]]\n|match_DIN_DGD=3\u20133\n|match_DIN_LIE=0\u20130\n|match_DIN_R\u012aG=3\u20131\n|match_DIN_SKO=0\u20131\n|match_DIN_VEN=0\u20133\n|match_DIN_VEN_note=The match originally finished 0\u20130, but was eventually awarded with as won by a score of 3\u20130 to [[FK Ventspils|Ventspils]] because [[Dinaburg FC]] fielded player who was not in match protocol.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.apollo.lv/portal/sports/articles/136993 |title=\u00abDinaburg\u00bb pie\u0161\u0137irts tehniskais zaud\u0113jums |access-date=2009-03-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717113105/http://www.apollo.lv/portal/sports/articles/136993 |archive-date=2011-07-17 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n|name_LIE=[[FK Liep\u0101jas Metalurgs|SK Liep\u0101jas Metalurgs]]\n|match_LIE_DGD=3\u20131\n|match_LIE_DIN=3\u20131\n|match_LIE_R\u012aG=3\u20130\n|match_LIE_SKO=0\u20130\n|match_LIE_VEN=1\u20132\n\n|name_R\u012aG=[[FK R\