\u00e9t]]\n| album         = <!-- NOT a proper single from the album, neither the Japanese version. Being included and being *released as a single* are not the same thing -->\n| released      = {{Start date|2019|04|01}}\n| recorded      = February 1, 2019<ref name=\"Genius\"/>\n| studio        = SpeakEasy Recording Studio [[Burbank, California]]\n| format        =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| genre         = [[Trap music|Trap]]-[[Pop music|pop]]<ref name=\"Uproxx\">{{Cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/music/ariana-grande-victoria-monet-monopoly-video/|title=Ariana Grande And Victoria Monet's 'Monopoly' Is A Celebratory Trap-Pop Banger|author=Chloe Gilke|publisher=Uproxx|date=1 April 2019|accessdate=2 April 2019}}</ref>\n| length        = {{duration|m=2|s=38}}\n| label         = [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n| writer        = <!--See Talk:Monopoly_(song)#Songwriters order -->\n* Victoria Mon\u00e9t\n* Ariana Grande\n* Tim Suby\n* [[Social House|Charles Anderson]]\n* [[Social House|Michael Foster]]\n| producer      =\n* Tim Suby\n* [[Social House]] ({{abbr|co.|co-producers}})\n| chronology    = [[Ariana Grande]]\n| prev_title    = [[Imagine (Ariana Grande song)|Imagine]] \n| prev_year     = 2018\n| next_title    = \n| next_year     = \n| misc          = {{External music video|{{YouTube|t0pryRrJvfI|\"Monopoly\"}}|type=song}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Monopoly'''\" (stylized in [[all caps]]) is a song by American singers [[Ariana Grande]] and [[Victoria Mon\u00e9t]], released on April 1, 2019 through label [[Republic Records]]. The song was written by Grande, Mon\u00e9t, Charles Anderson, Michael Foster, and Tim Suby, with production being handled by [[Social House]] and Suby. The music video, which was shot on March 30, 2019 at [[Mohegan Sun]] in the hours leading up to a [[Sweetener World Tour|concert scheduled that night]], was released alongside the single, and was directed by Alfredo Flores and Ricky Alvarez.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t0pryRrJvfI | title=Ariana Grande and Victoria Mon\u00e9t - MONOPOLY | publisher=[[YouTube]] | date=April 1, 2019 | accessdate=April 1, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/ariana-grande-release-new-song-monopoly-next-week-2468420 | title=Ariana Grande to release new song 'Monopoly' next week | work=[[NME]] | date=March 28, 2019 | accessdate=April 1, 2019 | author=Daly, Rhian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/ariana-grande-fans-are-convinced-she-s-come-out-as-bisexual-in-leaked-monopoly-lyrics-a4106511.html | title=Ariana Grande Monopoly: fans convinced singer has come out as bisexual in leaked lyrics | work=[[London Evening Standard]] | date=April 1, 2019 | accessdate=April 1, 2019 | author=Rosseinsky, Katie}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.wtnh.com/entertainment/ariana-grande-shot-monopoly-music-video-at-mohegan-sun/1894489843 | title=Ariana Grande shot \"Monopoly\" music video at Mohegan Sun | work=[[WTNH]] | date=April 2, 2019 | accessdate=April 2, 2019 | author=Ceneviva, Alex}}</ref>\n\n\"Monopoly\" was included on the Japanese [[Special edition|deluxe edition]] of Grande's fifth studio album ''[[Thank U, Next]]'' (2019) as a bonus track, along with the official remix of \"[[7 Rings]]\" featuring [[2 Chainz]].<ref name=\"universal japan\">{{cite web |title=\u30a2\u30ea\u30a2\u30ca\u30fb\u30b0\u30e9\u30f3\u30c7\u306e\u5927\u30d2\u30c3\u30c8\u30fb\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u300ethank u, next\u300f\u306e\u30c7\u30e9\u30c3\u30af\u30b9\u30fb\u30a8\u30c7\u30a3\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u304c\u3001\u65e5\u672c\u306e\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\u306e\u70ba\u3060\u3051\u306b\u30ea\u30ea\u30fc\u30b9\u6c7a\u5b9a\uff01\u305d\u306e\"\u7279\u5225\u306a\u767a\u58f2\u65e5\"\u3068\u306f\uff01\uff1f |trans-title=Ariana Grande's blockbuster album \"thank u, next\" deluxe edition is released only for Japanese fans! When is the special release date?|url=https://www.universal-music.co.jp/ariana-grande/news/2019-05-27/ |website=[[Universal Music Group|Universal Music Japan]] |accessdate=30 May 2019 |language=Japanese |date=27 May 2019}}</ref> It reached the top 5 in Greece and Israel and the top 20 in Ireland, Japan and New Zealand. The singers performed the song on some of the shows of the [[Sweetener World Tour]].\n\n==Background==\nMon\u00e9t and Grande decided to make a song titled \"Monopoly\", finding it funny since Mon\u00e9t dislikes the [[Monopoly (game)|board game]] and declines to play whenever Grande asks. The song was recorded on February 1, 2019.<ref name=\"Genius\">{{Cite AV media|author=[[Victoria Mon\u00e9t]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rmh_gVKJgE8|title=Victoria Mon\u00e9t \"MONOPOLY\" Official Lyrics & Meaning \u2013 Verified|publisher=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|date=2 May 2019|accessdate=24 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n\"Monopoly\" was originally slated for a March 28, 2019 release<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1111089219127132160|author=Ariana Grande|title=man, let's drop it tomorrow night @VictoriaMonet \ud83d\udda4 seven rings is ab to be number one for eight weeks and the album might go back to no. 1 too.... we need to celebrate tbh ! life too short and too sweet rn. hmmmmmmm.|accessdate=30 May 2019|date=27 March 2019|user=ArianaGrande}}</ref> but was pushed back to April 1, 2019 to celebrate \"[[7 Rings]]\" 8th week at number one on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/VictoriaMonet/status/1111173404378333184|title=Victoria Mon\u00e9t on Twitter: \"Yoo lets drop it Monday so we can celebrate an 8th week at number 1!!Cause this shit is insaaaane\"|accessdate=30 May 2019|author=Victoria Mon\u00e9t|publisher=[[Twitter]]|date=28 March 2019}}</ref> Grande said \"Monopoly\" is about \"friendship, freedom, protecting your energy and staying right in your bag.\"<ref name=\"PF\"/>\n\n==Lyrics and composition==\n\"Monopoly\" is a [[trap music|trap]]-[[pop music|pop]] song, leading ''[[Uproxx]]'' writer Chloe Gilke to call it the \"spiritual successor\" to Grande's single \"[[7 Rings]]\" which Mon\u00e9t also co-wrote. The song is a celebration of Grande's success, much like \"7 Rings\", which charted at number one on the Hot 100 for eight weeks.<ref name=\"Uproxx\"/>\n\nThe lyric \"I like women and men\" garnered significant attention since Mon\u00e9t previously [[Coming out|came out]] as [[bisexual]] in November 2018, referencing [[Frank Ocean]]'s 2017 single \"[[Chanel (Frank Ocean song)|Chanel]]\" which is about his own bisexuality.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/VictoriaMonet/status/1061037465174073344|title=Victoria Mon\u00e9t on Twitter: \"I want everyone to know that I'm single (since people wanna pretend I'm not) and make imaginary rules for me. I secretly and respectfully went through a difficult break up this summer but enough is enough. I also like girls. Thank U, Next. Bye \u270c\ud83c\udffe\"|publisher=[[Twitter]]|author=Victoria Mon\u00e9t|accessdate=30 May 2019|date=9 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/victoriamonet/status/1061110753061552129|author=Victoria Mon\u00e9t|accessdate=30 May 2019|date=9 November 2018|title=Victoria Mon\u00e9t on Twitter: \"See both sides like Chanel\"|publisher=[[Twitter]]}}</ref> Mon\u00e9t personally believed it was important to include this line, along with the lyrics \"Swerve both ways, [[Dichotomy]]\" (a [[double entendre]] invoking the word [[Dyke (slang)|dyke]]), to highlight her sexuality because of the lack of representation for bisexual black women in her industry.<ref name=\"Genius\"/> In response to the attention garnered by Grande for also singing the \"I like women and men\" line, Grande opened up about her sexuality and revealed she doesn't label herself, tweeting \"i haven\u2019t [labelled myself] before and still don\u2019t feel the need to now \ud83d\udda4\ud83e\uddda\ud83c\udffc\u200d\u2642\ufe0f which is okay\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.capitalfm.com/news/music/bisexual-new-song-monopoly-victoria-monet/|date=2 April 2019|accessdate=30 May 2019|title=Ariana Grande Responds To Speculation She's Bisexual After Telling 'Monopoly' Lyrics|publisher=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital FM]]}}</ref>\n\nGrande also sings \"Even though we gave up that 90%\", referencing the fact that she had to give up 90% of the royalties for \"7 Rings\" to [[Rodgers and Hammerstein]] due to [[Interpolation (popular music)|interpolating]] the melody of ''[[The Sound of Music]]''{{'}}s \"[[My Favorite Things (song)|My Favorite Things]]\".<ref name=\"PF\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/ariana-grande-and-victoria-monet-drop-new-song-monopoly-listen/|title=Ariana Grande and Victoria Mon\u00e9t Drop New Song \"Monopoly\": Listen|accessdate=30 May 2019|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=1 April 2019|author1=Evan Minsker|author2=Matthew Strauss}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]] praised the song and music video for being a \"meme-heavy bisexual bop\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/04/ariana-grande-monopoly-music-video.html|title=Ariana Grande and Victoria Mon\u00e9t Provide a Meme-Heavy Bisexual Bop With Their 'Monopoly' Video|publisher=Vulture|date=1 April 2019|accessdate=5 April 2019|author=Jackson McHenry}}</ref> ''[[NME]]'' wrote that following the release of ''[[Thank U, Next]]'' (2019), \"Monopoly\" was refreshing to hear, describing the song as \"flippant and fun\".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/ariana-grande-victoria-monet-monopoly-track-review-2470425#4dTPmWOow6JDLeSg.99|title=Ariana Grande and Victoria Mon\u00e9t's 'Monopoly' banishes fake friends away from the board|author=El Hunt|date=2 April 2019|accessdate=5 April 2019|magazine=NME}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Washington Post]]'', ''[[Vice Media|Broadly]]'', and ''[[PinkNews]]'' reported that certain fans responded negatively to the song, accusing Grande of [[queerbaiting]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/express/2019/04/02/trending-how-about-if-ariana-grande-doesnt-want-be-labeled-we-dont-label-her/?noredirect=on|title=Trending: How about if Ariana Grande doesn't want to be labeled, we don't label her.|author=Briana Ellison|date=2 April 2019|accessdate=5 April 2019|newspaper=The Washington Post}}</ref><ref name=\"Broadly\">{{Cite news|url=https://broadly.vice.com/en_us/article/nexa8q/ariana-grande-bisexual-monopoly-song|title=Why Everyone Is Obsessed With Ariana Grande's Bicurious Songs|date=5 April 2019|accessdate=5 April 2019|publisher=Broadly|author=Gabrielle Alexa}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2019/04/02/ariana-grande-queerbaiting-monopoly/|newspaper=PinkNews|title=Ariana Grande accused of 'queerbaiting' in new song 'Monopoly'|author=Ella Braidwood|date=2 April 2019|accessdate=3 April 2019}}</ref> ''Broadly'' writer Gabrielle Alexa criticized the accusations, stating \"the act of speculating only perpetuates attitudes that contribute to the [[Bisexual erasure|erasure of bisexual women]]. Grande doesn't have to date a girl in order to count as bisexual. And we shouldn't try to make her prove her sexuality anyways.\"<ref name=\"Broadly\"/>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>[https://listen.tidal.com/album/106798576 MONOPOLY / Ariana Grande \u2013 TIDAL]</ref>\n\n*[[Ariana Grande]] \u2013 vocals, songwriting\n*[[Victoria Mon\u00e9t]] \u2013 vocals, songwriting\n*Tim Suby \u2013 production, songwriting, programming\n*[[Social House]] \u2013 co-production, songwriting, programming\n*[[Kyle Mann]] \u2013 engineering, mixing, studio personnel\n*Brendan Morawski \u2013 engineering, studio personnel\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|21|artist=Ariana Grande & Victoria Mon\u00e9t|song=Monopoly|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 13, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders Tip|12|artist=Ariana Grande & Victoria Mon\u00e9t|song=Monopoly|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 4, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|37|artist=Ariana Grande & Victoria Mon\u00e9t|song=Monopoly|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 26, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|38|artist=Ariana Grande|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 16, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| China Airplay/FL (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboardchina.cn/top/radiocharts/2019-04-29.html|title=China Airplay Chart/Foreign Language - 29/04/2019|work=[[Billboard China]]|language=Chinese|accessdate=May 9, 2019}}</ref>\n| 26\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|45|year=2019|week=15|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 16, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|France|146|artist=Ariana Grande & Victoria Mon\u00e9t|song=Monopoly|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 15, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Germany2|98|songid=1857497|artist=Ariana Grande & Victoria Mon\u00e9t|song=Monopoly|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 12, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Greece ([[IFPI Greece|IFPI]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417220756/https://www.ifpi.gr/digital_iel.html|title=IFPI Charts|date=2019-04-17|website=web.archive.org|access-date=April 17, 2019}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarysingle|28|year=2019|week=14|artist=Ariana Grande & Victoria Mon\u00e9t|song=Monopoly|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 12, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarystream|25|year=2019|week=15|artist=Ariana Grande & Victoria Mon\u00e9t|song=Monopoly|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland3|15|artist=Ariana Grande|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 13, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Israel ([[Media Forest]] TV Airplay)<ref name=\"israelcharts\">{{cite web |title=\u05de\u05d3\u05d9\u05d4 \u05e4\u05d5\u05e8\u05e1\u05d8 - \u05dc\u05d3\u05e2\u05ea \u05e9\u05d0\u05ea\u05d4 \u05d1\u05d0\u05d5\u05d5\u05d9\u05e8 |publisher=Mediaforest.biz |accessdate=May 25, 2019| ur